CERTIFICATE OF RESULTS OF ELECTION
SECRETARIAL ELECTION
KICKAPOO TRADITIONAL TRIBE OF TEXAS

 
 AUGUST 2, 2018

Under a Secretarial election authorized by Terry Bruner, Acting Regional Director, on May 22, 2018, the 
attached Amendment A to the Constitution of the Kickapoo Traditional Tribe of Texas was submitted to the 
Registered voters of the Kickapoo Traditional Tribe of Texas and on August 2, 2018, duly and was 
adopted by a vote of 175 For and 45 Against, with 0 cast ballots found spoiled 

in an election which at least thirty percent (30%) of the 348 eligible voters cast their ballots in accordance 
with Article XII of the Constitution of the Kickapoo Traditional Tribe of Texas and the Indian Reorganization 
Act of June 18, 1934, 48 Stat. 984, as amended.

Date: August 2, 2018

United States Department of the Interior 
Bureau of Indian Affairs 
Southern Plains Regional Office 
P.O. Box 368 
Anadarko, Oklahoma 73005
 
 

AMENDMENT A
SECRETARIAL ELECTION
KICKAPOO TRADITIONAL TRIBE OF TEXAS

 
 AUGUST 2, 2018

The Constitution of the Kickapoo Traditional Tribe of Texas amended to:

Article II Membership, Section 2.

From and after the adoption of this Constitution, persons who are members of other federally 
recognized Indian Tribes who are at least % degree Kickapoo Indian blood may apply for 
membership in the Tribe provided: 1) they have relinquished their membership in the other 
Tribe; 2) they have resided within the jurisdiction of the Tribe as defined in Article I for ten (10) 
years; and 3) the application for membership is approved by the Membership Committee.
 
 

NUMERICAL DESIGNATION

 
 Having been duly adopted and approved, proposed Amendment A is hereby designated as Amendment No.
II to the Constitution of the Kickapoo Traditional Tribe of Texas.

United States Department of the Interior
 
 

