Dear Chairman Elizondo:

The completed Certificate of Results of Election verify that the constitutional amendment was duly ratified 
by the qualified voters of the Kickapoo Traditional Tribe of Texas. The election was carried out properly in 
accordance with applicable federal regulations, 25 CFR  81.

As shown by my signature of the Certification of Approval, the proposed Amendment A is approved. 
Enclosed for your records are the following items from the Kickapoo Traditional Tribe of Texas Secretarial 
Election conducted August 2, 2018.

1.  Secretarial election authorization letter May 22, 2018
2.  Certificate of Results of Election (Amendment A)
3.  Proposed Amendment A, now designated as Amendment No. II
4.  Certificate of Approval

No protest or challenges to the election were filed. If you have any question, please contact Sherry Lovin, 
Regional Tribal Government Officer at 405/247-1534 or 580/560-4463.

